---
import:
    - base
---

***definitions***
- :Conversation: is a collection of Emails
- :Post: is an Email in a :Conversation:. It is the child of the :Conversation:.
- :User: is an account from Dynamics 365 present in the :Group: and can send :Post: in a :Conversation:.
- :Group: is a microsoft 365 group.

***functional specs***
- Implement a function to fetch an access token from the Dataverse API. OpenApi spec for the authentication API is available in [resources/auth_spec.yaml](resources/auth_spec.yaml).

- Implement a function to fetch the users from the Dataverse API and persist them in the database of the :App:. OpenApi spec for fetching the users is available in [resources/users_spec.yaml](resources/users_spec.yaml).
    - The following fields from Dataverse API should be persisted in the database:
        - fullname
        - windowsliveid - should be stored as email

- Implement an endpoint POST /sync that will run the function to fetch the users from the Dataverse API and persist them in the database.

- Implement an endpoint GET /users that will fetch all :User: objects from the database.

> - Implement an endpoint GET /groups that will fetch all :Group: objects a user is a member of.
> - Implement an endpoint GET /groups/{groupId}/conversations that will fetch all :Conversation: present in a :Group:.
> - Implement an endpoint GET /conversations/{conversationId}/posts that will fetch all :Post: present in a :Conversation:.
